HEADWORD: Cavatina
<hw>Ca`va*ti"na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>Originally, a melody of simpler form than the
<xex>aria</xex>; a song without a second part and a <xex>da capo</xex>;
-- a term now variously and vaguely used.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

